CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 10, 1955, pg. 4 reads: "Protest Rezoning - City Council heard arguments, pro and con, Tuesday, concerning the proposed ordinance to change from Class "B" to "A" property bounded by Chalfont Street, Delmont Avenue, Bolivar Way and Gearing Avenue, in the Eighteenth Ward (Beltzhoover), that wouldn't permit the establishment of a funeral home at 616 Delmont Avenue...upper center, Beltzhoover residents attending the hearing in Council Chambers...-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women and men seated for Beltzhoover rezoning Pittsburgh City Council Chambers at the City County Building
